HEADWORD: Clydesdale
<hw>Clydes"dale</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One of a breed of
heavy draft horses originally from Clydesdale, Scotland. They are about
sixteen hands high and usually brown or bay.</def>⟦br⟧
